<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Sample Web Page</title>

    <!-- Google Fonts -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        h1, h2 {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- First-level heading -->
    <h1>Welcome to My Sample Web Page</h1>

    <!-- Second-level heading -->
    <h2>About This Page</h2>

    <!-- Paragraph -->
    <p>This page demonstrates the use of HTML tags, lists, links, Google Fonts, and the Bootstrap framework.</p>

    <!-- Numbered list -->
    <h2>Steps to Learn HTML</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Understand basic tags like headings and paragraphs.</li>
        <li>Learn how to create lists and links.</li>
        <li>Use Google Fonts for custom typography.</li>
        <li>Add Bootstrap for styling and layout.</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Bulleted list -->
    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Responsive design with Bootstrap</li>
        <li>Custom fonts from Google Fonts</li>
        <li>Semantic HTML structure</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Link -->
    <p>Visit <a href="https://getbootstrap.com" target="_blank">Bootstrap Official Site</a> for more details.</p>

    <!-- Bootstrap Button -->
    <button class="btn btn-primary">Click Me</button>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS (Optional) -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
